description.text:
Related #106229. The color-shape protocol allows us to not have to deal with cursor theming and instead depend on the compositor for it.
This still does not quite solve the issue when the compositor doesn't implement the protocol (or running under the x11 backend) but for gnome/kde and a few more this should resolve things.

@Chapien On breeze I can get the normal pointer, text input and renames but can't quite remember where else to hover to get more cursors so how is this running for you?

### Tested versions

- Reproducible in v4.4.1.stable.mono.official [49a5bc7b6], v4.5.dev3.mono.official [28089c40c], v4.3.stable.mono.official [77dcf97d8]
- Could not reproduce in v4.2.2.stable.mono.official [15073afe3]
  - Most likely due to additional support for generics, like https://github.com/godotengine/godot/pull/87890, not this bug as the whole resource breaks and there are errors

### System information

Godot v4.4.1.stable.mono.official - macOS Sequoia (15.4.1) - Multi-window, 1 monitor - Metal (Mobile) - integrated Apple M1 Pro (Apple7) - Apple M1 Pro (10 threads)

### Issue description

When making a build, `_Get` has a the generic value set to `null` (even though it's set in the `.tres` file). This results in the inspector losing the value upon build. I'm not sure what the requirements are, but I have nested the generics like so to reproduce:
```cs
// Item.cs
[GlobalClass]
[Tool]
public partial class Item : Resource
{
    [Export]
    public string Title { get; set; }
}
```

```cs
// WeightedItem.cs
[Tool]
public partial class WeightedItem<[MustBeVariant] T> : Resource
{
    public T Item { get; set; }
    public float Weight { get; set; }
}
```

This is the key class, handling the Get & Set that fails.
```cs
// WeightContainer.cs
[Tool]
public partial class WeightContainer<[MustBeVariant] T> : Resource
{
    private Array<WeightedItem<T>> _list;

    private int _size;

    [Export]
    public int Count
    {
        get => _size;
        set
        {
            _size = value;
            _list.Resize(_size);
            NotifyPropertyListChanged();
        }
    }

    public override Array<Dictionary> _GetPropertyList()
    {
        Array<Dictionary> properties = [];

        for (var i = 0; i < _size; i++)
        {
            properties.Add(new Dictionary()
            {
                { "name", $"list_{i}/Item" },
                { "type", (int)Variant.Type.Object },
                { "hint", (int)PropertyHint.ResourceType },
                { "hint_string", typeof(T).Name },
                { "usage", (int)PropertyUsageFlags.Editor + (int)PropertyUsageFlags.Storage + (int)PropertyUsageFlags.StoreIfNull }
            });
            properties.Add(new Dictionary()
            {
                { "name", $"list_{i}/Weight" },
                { "type", (int)Variant.Type.Float },
                { "hint", (int)PropertyHint.Range },
                { "hint_string", "0,20,,or_greater,hide_slider" },
                { "usage", (int)PropertyUsageFlags.Editor + (int)PropertyUsageFlags.Storage }
            });
        }

        return properties;
    }

    public override Variant _Get(StringName property)
    {
        var propertyName = property.ToString();
        if (propertyName.StartsWith("list_"))
        {
            string[] split = propertyName.Split('/');
            int index = int.Parse(split[0]["list_".Length..]);
            _list[index] ??= new WeightedItem<T>();
            switch (split[1])
            {
                case "Weight":
                    return _list[index].Weight;
                case "Item":
                    return Variant.From(_list[index].Item);
                default:
                    GD.PrintErr("Invalid property name in WeightedList for WeightedItem: " + split[1]);
                    break;
            }
        }

        return default;
    }

    public override bool _Set(StringName property, Variant value)
    {
        var propertyName = property.ToString();
        if (propertyName.StartsWith("list_"))
        {
            string[] split = propertyName.Split('/');
            int index = int.Parse(split[0]["list_".Length..]);
            _list[index] ??= new WeightedItem<T>();
            switch (split[1])
            {
                case "Weight":
                    _list[index].Weight = value.As<float>();
                    NotifyPropertyListChanged();
                    return true;
                case "Item":
                    _list[index].Item = value.As<T>();
                    NotifyPropertyListChanged();
                    return true;
                default:
                    GD.PrintErr("Invalid property name in WeightedList for WeightedItem: " + split[1]);
                    break;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```

Upon building the project (not exporting), in `_Get`, and `_GetPropertyList`, `_list[0].Item` is `null`. Once set it's loaded correctly, and saved to the resource, until the next build. Updating the resource's `.tres` file (specifically the weight) will update the editor and cause it to load `Item` correctly.

### Steps to reproduce

1. Open the MRP
2. Build the project
3. Open node.tres (if not already open)
4. Open `Box.tres` in the editor and set `List_0/Item` to `ExampleItem.tres`
  - It should already be set in `Box.tres` file, this updates the editor to match
5. Save
6. Build
  - As you haven't changed any scripts, you will have to. In `Item.cs:13` there's a useless variable you can change the name of to get the project to build all scripts.
7. Observe the inspector clearing the value for `List_0/Item`. It will still be saved in `Box.tres`.

If there's an error on building, or the inspect doesn't display any fields for `Box.tres`, follow these steps to recreate it: (because it's a generic, you can't use `[GlobalClass]`)
1. Open `node.tres` and open `Node` in the inspector
2. Reset `Box` field.
3. Set `Count` to `1`.
4. Save `Box` value as a new resource (I named it `Box.tres`)
This lets you save and edit resources that utilise generics.

### Minimal reproduction project (MRP)

[testgenericget.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/20105819/testgenericget.zip)
